title: Piratsy Under the Seas
description: Dale accidentally falls into a city garbage truck while cleaning up.

title: Catteries Not Included
description: The Rescue Rangers help a little girl find her kidnapped kitten.

title: Dale Beside Himself
description: At the end of their vacation to Earth, one of three aliens decides to stay.

title: Flash the Wonder Dog
description: One of the most popular television shows is "Flash the Wonder Dog." However, animal villain Fat Cat has grown tired of Flash's heroic antics, and has the dog-actor kidnapped. Donning disguises to make them resemble Flash, Fat Cat and his minions attempt to tarnish the dog's good name. The Rescue Rangers decide to find the real Flash at Dale's behest, but what will happen when the eager chipmunk realizes his hero isn't a real hero after all?

title: Out to Launch
description: The Rescue Rangers visit the Space Center to watch a launch.

title: Kiwi's Big Adventure
description: Deep in the jungle, a tribe of kiwi birds have stolen the Ranger Plane.

title: Adventures in Squirrelsitting
description: While in pursuit of the famed Maltese Mouse, the Rescue Rangers accidentally wreck the home of a family of squirrels. While the Mother squirrel straightens up her abode, the Rangers offer to take care of the squirrel children, Tammy and Bink. While Monterey Jack and Dale tend to little Bink, Chip has his hands full trying to deal with Tammy, who has developed a crush on him.

title: Pound of the Baskervilles
description: The Ranger Plane crashes into the Baskerville Mansion.

title: Risky Beesness
description: When a prissy Queen Bee finds her hive of workers have been stolen, she goes to the Rescue Rangers for help. Zipper is also eager to help, and develops a crush on the beautiful Queen Bee as well.

title: Three Men and a Booby
description: While on a shopping spree, the Rescue Rangers meet a rare booby bird.

title: The Carpetsnaggers
description: A flying doghouse puts the Rescue Rangers on the trail of Ali Bimbo.

title: Bearing Up Baby
description: While on vacation, a young camper, befriends a bear.

title: Parental Discretion Retired
description: The Rangers go to the docks to meet Monterey's dad, Cheddarhead Charlie.

title: Rescue Rangers to the Rescue: Part 1
description: Chip and Dale follow their friend, master Detective Donald Drake.

title: Rescue Rangers to the Rescue: Part 2
description: At a Chinatown laundry, Fat Cat buys the #1 Siamese fighting fish.

title: Rescue Rangers to the Rescue: Part 3
description: Fat Cat runs to the airport to replace the ruby in Klordane's jewelry case.

title: Rescue Rangers to the Rescue: Part 4
description: The Rangers take the ruby from the laser cannon in order to clear Drake.

title: Rescue Rangers to the Rescue: Part 5
A Lad in a Lamp
description: Fat Cat smuggles a magic lamp into the country.

title: The Luck Stops Here
description: Clyde Cosgrove, accidentally scoops Gadget into his briefcase.

title: Battle of the Bulge
description: The Rescue Rangers learn about mysterious mid-air robberies.

title: Ghost of a Chance
description: The Rescue Rangers follow Fat Cat and his minions to the Tower of London.

description: The Rangers investigate missing peanuts at the zoo.

title: Fake Me to Your Leader
description: Zipper is accidentally zapped by Professor Nimnul's "gigantico ray" gun.

title: A Case of Stage Blight
description: Dale drags the Rangers to a movie theater that is actually an opera house.

title: The Case of the Cola Cult
description: While testing the new Rangermobile, the Rangers crash into a Cola Factory.

title: Throw Mummy from the Train
description: At the tomb of King Nutun-Khamun, an archaeologist finds the ring to unlock the diamonds of the Sphinx of Inka-dinka-do. His greedy assistant Wexler steals the ring and eludes the mummy assigned to guard it, Hiram. Wexler tries to hide the ring and Dale gets it for a while, putting the Rangers on the case.

title: A Wolf in Cheap Clothing
description: Dale's is convinced that a werewolf is committing robberies!

title: Robocat
description: A junkman invents the ultimate mouse trap, a robot cat named Tom.

title: Does Pavlov Ring a Bell
description: Chip and Dale are jealous of Gadget's attentions for a spaced-out lab rat.

description: A group of paleontologists discover what they believe is a dinosaur egg.

description: The Rangers investigate a series of bizarre attacks on seafood restaurants.

description: The Rescue Rangers visit Cassandra, a fortune-telling Gypsy moth.

description: The Rescue Rangers get shipwrecked on a deserted island.

description: The Rangers travel to the town of Tramplonia for the running of the bulls.

title: Chocolate Chips
description: in a South American jungle, the Cacao trees are mysteriously disappearing.
